OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1777107988
OL,3,CAssisted dying bill fails after
OL,4,Crunning out of time in House of Lords
OL,6,FAssisted dying will not become law in
OL,7,FEngland and Wales after proposed
OL,8,Flegislation branded "hopelessly
OL,9,Fflawed" by opponents ran out of time
OL,10,Fin the House of Lords, with some peers
OL,11,Faccused of deliberately
OL,13,FThe Terminally Ill Adults (End of
OL,14,FLife) Bill, which had been making its
OL,15,Fway through Parliament for the past
OL,16,Fyear and a half, fell on Friday, with
OL,17,Fpeers in the House of Lords speaking
OL,18,Fpassionately on both sides of the
OL,19,Fargument.
OL,26,@pD@UOUqD@GO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1777107988
OL,3,CAssisted dying bill fails after
OL,4,Crunning out of time in House of Lords
OL,6,FWhile the bill had successfully passed
OL,7,Ftwo votes in the House of Commons,
OL,8,Falbeit with a narrower majority on the
OL,9,Fsecond occasion, it did not face a
OL,10,Fvote in the Lords.
OL,12,FIt instead ran out of time, with Lord
OL,13,FCharlie Falconer ` who had steered it
OL,14,Fthrough the upper chamber ` saying he
OL,15,Ffelt "despondent" that a piece of
OL,16,Flegislation which he said was "so
OL,17,Fimportant to so many, has not failed
OL,18,Fon its merits, but failed as a result
OL,19,Fof procedural wrangling".
OL,26,@wD@FOUwD@QO]xD@_OU{D@XO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1777107988
OL,3,CAssisted dying bill fails after
OL,4,Crunning out of time in House of Lords
OL,6,FThe bill had proposed allowing adults
OL,7,Fin England and Wales, with fewer than
OL,8,Fsix months to live, to apply for an
OL,9,Fassisted death, subject to the
OL,10,Fapproval of two doctors and an expert
OL,11,Fpanel.
OL,13,FMore than 1,200 amendments to the bill
OL,14,Fhad been suggested in the Lords, with
OL,15,Fmore than 800 of those tabled or
OL,16,Fsponsored by seven peers.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1777107988
OL,3,CAssisted dying bill fails after
OL,4,Crunning out of time in House of Lords
OL,6,FLord Falconer said the bill had not
OL,7,Ffailed to finish its journey through
OL,8,Fthe Lords due to a lack of time, but
OL,9,Frather "because a small minority were
OL,10,Fnot willing to cooperate, as we
OL,11,Fnormally do, to ensure that there can
OL,12,Fbe proportionate debate".
OL,14,FTory former cabinet minister Lord
OL,15,FBaker of Dorking accused opponents of
OL,16,Fthe bill of a "prolonged filibuster",
OL,17,Fbranding the situation a "denial of
OL,18,Fdemocracy".
OL,26,@qD@HOUtD@XO]xD@OOUxD@dO]yD@ZOUzD@JO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
