PN,31111
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1777107988
OL,3,CAssisted dying bill fails after
OL,4,Crunning out of time in House of Lords
OL,6,FThe Archbishop of Canterbury, who sits
OL,7,Fin the Lords and has spoken out
OL,8,Fagainst the bill, said: "There is no
OL,9,Fdoubt in my mind that this is one of
OL,10,Fthe biggest societal shifts that we
OL,11,Fare seeing or will see. Therefore, as
OL,12,Fwe have done, we need to take our role
OL,13,Fseriously."
OL,15,FThe government remained neutral on the
OL,16,Fissue and MPs voted according to their
OL,17,Fconsciences rather than along party
OL,18,Flines, but one Conservative peer said
OL,19,Fhe had been told by some Labour MPs
OL,20,Fthey "felt intimidated" into voting in
OL,21,Ffavour of it.
OL,26,@pD@YOUuD@KO]|D@FOU|D@WO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
