OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1777107988
OL,3,CAssisted dying bill fails after
OL,4,Crunning out of time in House of Lords
OL,6,FPrime Minister Sir Keir Starmer voted
OL,7,Fin favour while Conservative leader
OL,8,FKemi Badenoch voted against.
OL,10,FFormer Tory treasurer Lord Farmer told
OL,11,Fthe Lords: "I've spoken to a number of
OL,12,FLabour MPs since, and what was not
OL,13,Fknown, possibly, is that there was
OL,14,Fconsiderable pressure from Number 10
OL,15,F(to) pass the Bill."
OL,26,@sD@LOUwD@TO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
