OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1777107988
OL,3,CAssisted dying bill fails after
OL,4,Crunning out of time in House of Lords
OL,6,FAsked by reporters on Friday if the PM
OL,7,Fwas disappointed to see the bill fall,
OL,8,Fa Number 10 spokesperson said: "He's
OL,9,Fspoken about the importance of the
OL,10,Fgovernment being neutral on the issue,
OL,11,Ftherefore, explained why he hasn't
OL,12,Fspoken on it.
OL,14,F"As a result, it's a matter for MPs,
OL,15,Fit's a matter for parliamentarians,
OL,16,Fand that remains the case."
OL,18,FMs Badenoch has said the Bill should
OL,19,Fnot be brought back in the next
OL,20,Fparliamentary session, describing it
OL,21,Fas "hopelessly flawed".
OL,26,@pD@`OUvD@AOUxD@[O]}D@DOU}D@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/18
